# /goal condition template
#
# Fill the {{PLACEHOLDER}} fields for the target project, then pass the resulting
# text verbatim as the argument to `/goal`. The evaluator only judges by this exact
# text against the conversation so far — nothing here is enforced unless it is
# written into the condition itself. All four stop signals below are mandatory;
# do not ship a condition with only the success clause.
#
# {{JUDGE_CLAUSE}}: only include a judge sub-clause in the success condition when
# this task has any criterion that needs semantic/visual judgment (does it look
# right, does it read correctly, is the behavior actually acceptable) rather than
# a plain deterministic check. Use generic field names in that sub-clause —
# `verdict`/`pass`, not something UI-specific like `rendered` — since the judge
# may be evaluating text, an API response, a file diff, or a screenshot depending
# on the task. If every criterion is deterministic, leave {{JUDGE_CLAUSE}} empty
# (the sentence still reads fine ending on "allPass=true)."): the success stop
# then depends only on evidence.json's allPass, and no judge subagent is spawned
# at all (per the cost-control principle — a judge subagent is a real cost, not
# a default step). When it does apply, fill it with something like:
#   , and the independent judge subagent has returned a structured verdict
#   (verdict=pass, issues empty or all known-exempt)

Success stop: {{SUCCESS_CRITERIA}}, and the conversation has posted verify.sh's evidence.json (allPass=true){{JUDGE_CLAUSE}}.

Safety stop: {{MAX_TURNS}} turns have elapsed without reaching the success stop above — stop immediately, report which acceptance criteria are met/pending, and do not keep attempting.

No-progress stop: the criteriaMet list has shown zero change for {{NO_PROGRESS_TURNS}} (default 3) consecutive turns — stop immediately and report exactly which criterion is stuck and the most recent concrete error.

Blocked escalation: something has come up that only a human can resolve (missing credentials, a license/signing prompt, a request outside the authorized scope such as needing to touch backend code or run git push) — stop immediately, report the blocker, and do not spend remaining turns trying to work around it.

{{SCOPE_EXEMPTIONS}}  <!-- Example: "known-unfixable network/CORS failures are exempt and do not count against allPass" -->

Do not declare the task complete unless every clause of the success stop is satisfied.
